.TH "tty_port_install" 9 "tty_port_install" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tty_port_install \- generic tty->ops->install handler
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" tty_port_install
.BI "(struct tty_port *port "  ","
.BI "struct tty_driver *driver "  ","
.BI "struct tty_struct *tty "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "port" 12
tty_port of the device
.IP "driver" 12
tty_driver for this device
.IP "tty" 12
tty to be installed
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
It is the same as tty_standard_install except the provided \fIport\fP is linked
to a concrete tty specified by \fItty\fP. Use this or tty_port_register_device
(or both). Call tty_port_link_device as a last resort.
